        "description": "[ Found while investigating the impact of MAPREDUCE-2094 ]\n\nThe org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.lib.input.NLineInputFormat (probably the mapred version too) only makes sense for splittable files.\n\nThis inputformat uses the isSplitable from its superclass FileInputFormat (which always returns true) in combination with the LineRecordReader.\n\nWhen you provide it a gzipped file (non-splittable compression) it will create multiple splits (isSplitable == true) yet the LineRecordReader cannot handle the gzipped file in multiple splits because the GzipCodec does not support this.\n\nOverall effect is that you get incorrect results.\n\nProposed solution: Add detection for this kind of scenario and let the NLineInputFormat fail hard when someone tries this. \n\nI'm not sure if this should go into the LineRecordReader or only in the NLineInputFormat.\n\n\n\n",
